The pioneer Chairman of the Nigerian Bar Association (NBA) Section on Public Interest and Development Law (NBA-SPIDEL), Chief Joe-Kyari Gadzama (SAN), has commended Egbe Amofin O’odua for showing “an unwavering commitment to the protection and welfare of your members.” Chief Joe-Kyari Gadzama  “ I urge you all to participate effectively, cross-fertilise ideas whilst addressing issues that affect your distinguished members by contributing your quota to the promotion and development of your association and the legal practice,” he charged. Meanwhile, Gadzama has received Sir Ahmadu Bello Sardauna Sokoto Platinum Leadership Award from the Northern Youth Council of Nigeria (NYCN). The award was in recognition of his immense contribution towards purposeful leadership and youth development. NYCN stated that the learned silk has distinguished himself as a philanthropist and a legal practitioner dedicated to the advancement of legal profession. He was also recognised for his selfless service. Council also awarded Gadzama with the Medal of Honour as “Jarman Matassan Arewa (Icon and Cynosure of Judicial Transformation).